{"questionId":"21157","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A planet is in a circular orbit around a star. The speed of the planet is constant. The following&nbsp;data are given:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:120px;\">Mass of planet&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>24</mn></msup><mo> </mo></math>kg<br>Mass of star&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>30</mn></msup><mo> </mo></math>kg<br>Distance from the star to the planet <em>R</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>10</mn></msup><mo> </mo></math>m.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A spacecraft is to be launched from the surface of the planet to escape from the star&nbsp;system. The radius of the planet is 9.1 × 10<sup>3</sup> km.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Estimate the escape speed of the spacecraft from the planet–star system.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of <em>v</em><sub>esc</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>V</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p><em>v = </em>9.91&nbsp;× 10<sup>4</sup>&nbsp;«m s<sup>−1</sup>»&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"21157","referenceCode":"21M.2.HL.TZ1.2c.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Estimate the escape speed of the spacecraft from the planet–star system.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","